    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. looking at the data though, isn't there a pretty strong consensus among most mainstream economists that these kinds of supply-side cuts actually end up increasing inequality? it feels like the \"trickle down\" argument is often cited as being pretty debunked in recent years. what do the most recent empirical studies actually show about that link?",
